## A flower that sways, with petals that lag

A flower stem sways in the wind. The petals at the top lag behind the stem, bending and settling.

```scheme
(let* ((stem (world/spawn 200 220))
       (flower (world/spawn 200 160))
       (petal-1 (world/spawn 190 155))
       (petal-2 (world/spawn 210 155))
       (stem-angle 0)
       (flower-offset-x 0)
       (flower-vx 0)
       (petal-1-offset 0)
       (petal-2-offset 0)
       (petal-1-vx 0)
       (petal-2-vx 0)
       (t 0))
  (entity/sprite! stem \"circle\" 6 \"darkgreen\")
  (entity/sprite! flower \"circle\" 14 \"hotpink\")
  (entity/sprite! petal-1 \"circle\" 8 \"pink\")
  (entity/sprite! petal-2 \"circle\" 8 \"pink\")
  
  (world/after 1
    (lambda ()
      (set! t (+ t 0.06))
      
      ;; stem sways
      (set! stem-angle (* 0.4 (dsin t)))
      (let ((stem-x (+ 200 (* 30 (dsin stem-angle)))))
        (entity/set-pos! stem stem-x 220))
      
      ;; flower follows stem with lag
      (let* ((stem-x (entity/x stem))
             (target-x stem-x)
             (dx (- target-x (+ 200 flower-offset-x))))
        (set! flower-vx (+ flower-vx (* dx 0.10)))
        (set! flower-vx (* flower-vx 0.85))
        (set! flower-offset-x (+ flower-offset-x flower-vx))
        (entity/set-pos! flower (+ 200 flower-offset-x) 160))
      
      ;; petals lag behind flower
      (let* ((flower-x (entity/x flower))
             (p1-target (- flower-x 10))
             (p2-target (+ flower-x 10)))
        (let ((dx1 (- p1-target (+ 200 petal-1-offset))))
          (set! petal-1-vx (+ petal-1-vx (* dx1 0.08)))
          (set! petal-1-vx (* petal-1-vx 0.82))
          (set! petal-1-offset (+ petal-1-offset petal-1-vx)))
        (let ((dx2 (- p2-target (+ 200 petal-2-offset))))
          (set! petal-2-vx (+ petal-2-vx (* dx2 0.08)))
          (set! petal-2-vx (* petal-2-vx 0.82))
          (set! petal-2-offset (+ petal-2-offset petal-2-vx)))
        (entity/set-pos! petal-1 (+ 190 petal-1-offset) 155)
        (entity/set-pos! petal-2 (+ 210 petal-2-offset) 155))
      
      (when (<= (world/frame) 300)
        (world/after 1 (world/current-callback))))))
```

[VISUAL: Green circle at the bottom sways left and right. Pink circle above it lags behind the sway. Two smaller pink circles (petals) on either side lag even further, creating a cascading sway—stem, then flower, then petals.]

The petals are the final layer of secondary motion. They lag the flower, which lags the stem—three levels of follow-through, each with its own timing.

