## A chain of springs

Five springs hang vertically, connected end-to-end. The top is anchored. The bottom is pulled, stretching the chain. When released, the springs compress and oscillate, each with its own phase.

```scheme
(let* ((anchor-y 80)
       (springs (map (lambda (i)
                       (let ((s (world/spawn 200 (+ anchor-y (* i 25)))))
                         (entity/sprite! s \"circle\" 8 \"silver\")
                         (list s (+ anchor-y (* i 25)) 0)))  ;; (entity rest-y vy)
                     (list 0 1 2 3 4)))
       (pulled #f)
       (released #f))
  
  ;; pull at t=20
  (world/after 20
    (lambda ()
      (set! pulled #t)))
  
  ;; release at t=60
  (world/after 60
    (lambda ()
      (set! pulled #f)
      (set! released #t)))
  
  (world/after 1
    (lambda ()
      (if pulled
          ;; stretch: each spring pulls toward the one above + offset
          (set! springs
            (let loop ((segs springs)
                       (target-y anchor-y)
                       (i 0))
              (if (null? segs)
                  '()
                  (let* ((seg-data (car segs))
                         (seg (car seg-data))
                         (rest-y (cadr seg-data))
                         (vy (caddr seg-data))
                         (stretch-y (+ target-y (* i 35))))  ;; stretched spacing
                    (entity/set-pos! seg 200 stretch-y)
                    (cons (list seg rest-y vy)
                          (loop (cdr segs) stretch-y (+ i 1)))))))
          ;; spring back and oscillate
          (set! springs
            (map (lambda (seg-data)
                   (let* ((seg (car seg-data))
                          (rest-y (cadr seg-data))
                          (vy (caddr seg-data))
                          (current-y (entity/y seg))
                          (dy (- rest-y current-y))
                          (accel (* dy 0.1)))
                     (set! vy (+ vy accel))
                     (set! vy (* vy 0.92))
                     (entity/move! seg 0 vy)
                     (list seg rest-y vy)))
                 springs)))
      
      (when (<= (world/frame) 180)
        (world/after 1 (world/current-callback))))))
```

