### Cloak Corner Following a Shoulder

A character's shoulder moves in a square path; a single cloak corner lags behind.

```scheme
(let ((shoulder-x 200)
      (shoulder-y 200)
      (cloak-x 200)
      (cloak-y 200)
      (waypoints (list (cons 200 200) (cons 350 200) (cons 350 300) (cons 200 300)))
      (current-waypoint 0)
      (time 0))
  (motion/loop 300
    (lambda (frame)
      (set! time (+ time 1))
      (if (= (modulo time 60) 0)
          (set! current-waypoint (modulo (+ current-waypoint 1) (length waypoints))))
      (let* ((target (list-ref waypoints current-waypoint))
             (tx (car target))
             (ty (cdr target)))
        (set! shoulder-x (+ shoulder-x (* (- tx shoulder-x) 0.1)))
        (set! shoulder-y (+ shoulder-y (* (- ty shoulder-y) 0.1)))
        (set! cloak-x (+ cloak-x (* (- shoulder-x cloak-x) 0.06)))
        (set! cloak-y (+ cloak-y (* (- shoulder-y cloak-y) 0.06)))
        (world/clear)
        (entity/circle shoulder-x shoulder-y 8 \"navy\")
        (entity/circle cloak-x cloak-y 12 \"crimson\")
        (entity/line shoulder-x shoulder-y cloak-x cloak-y \"gray\")
        (world/paint)))))
```

[VISUAL: A navy dot (shoulder) traces a square, changing direction every 60 frames; a crimson circle (cloak corner) trails behind, rounding the corners smoothly.]

The cloak softens the sharp corners of the shoulder's path, arriving late and with a curve.

