### Damped Spring Chain

A leader snaps to a new position; two followers overshoot and settle.

```scheme
(let ((leader-x 200)
      (f1-x 200)
      (f1-vx 0)
      (f2-x 200)
      (f2-vx 0)
      (time 0))
  (motion/loop 180
    (lambda (frame)
      (set! time (+ time 1))
      (when (= time 40)
        (set! leader-x 400))
      (let ((spring1 (* (- leader-x f1-x) 0.08))
            (damp1 (* f1-vx 0.85))
            (spring2 (* (- f1-x f2-x) 0.08))
            (damp2 (* f2-vx 0.85)))
        (set! f1-vx (+ (* damp1 0.9) spring1))
        (set! f1-x (+ f1-x f1-vx))
        (set! f2-vx (+ (* damp2 0.9) spring2))
        (set! f2-x (+ f2-x f2-vx)))
      (world/clear)
      (entity/circle leader-x 200 10 \"darkgreen\")
      (entity/circle f1-x 220 8 \"olive\")
      (entity/circle f2-x 240 6 \"khaki\")
      (world/paint))))
```

[VISUAL: At frame 40, the green leader jumps right; the olive and khaki followers oscillate as they chase, overshooting and settling in a damped wave.]

Each follower has velocity and damping—so they *bounce* a little before settling.

