### Cloth Corner with Tension

A character moves; a cloth corner lags, but also pulls toward a fixed attachment point (tension).

```scheme
(let ((body-x 200)
      (corner-x 200)
      (anchor-x 150)
      (time 0))
  (motion/loop 160
    (lambda (frame)
      (set! time (+ time 1))
      (set! body-x (+ 200 (* 60 (sin (* time 0.05)))))
      (let* ((to-body (* (- body-x corner-x) 0.1))
             (to-anchor (* (- anchor-x corner-x) 0.03))
             (total (+ to-body to-anchor)))
        (set! corner-x (+ corner-x total)))
      (world/clear)
      (entity/circle anchor-x 200 5 \"black\")
      (entity/circle body-x 200 8 \"navy\")
      (entity/circle corner-x 220 6 \"cyan\")
      (entity/line anchor-x 200 corner-x 220 \"gray\")
      (entity/line body-x 200 corner-x 220 \"gray\")
      (world/paint))))
```

[VISUAL: A cyan corner is pulled by both a moving navy body and a fixed black anchor; it settles into a compromise position, oscillating slightly.]

The corner balances two competing forces—body motion and anchor tension—producing realistic cloth sag.

