### Rope Under Oscillation

A rope's top end oscillates; the bottom end follows with damped overshoot.

```scheme
(let ((top-x 250)
      (bottom-x 250)
      (bottom-vx 0)
      (time 0))
  (motion/loop 200
    (lambda (frame)
      (set! time (+ time 0.1))
      (set! top-x (+ 250 (* 50 (sin time))))
      (let ((spring (* (- top-x bottom-x) 0.12))
            (damp (* bottom-vx 0.88)))
        (set! bottom-vx (+ damp spring))
        (set! bottom-x (+ bottom-x bottom-vx)))
      (world/clear)
      (entity/line top-x 150 bottom-x 250 \"gray\")
      (entity/circle top-x 150 5 \"black\")
      (entity/circle bottom-x 250 7 \"darkgray\")
